==English==
===Noun===
'''yinzer'''
# A native of [[Pittsburgh]], [[Pennsylvania]].
==Etymology==
''Yinzer'' references the "Pittsburghese" dialect's use of ''yinz'' as the plural of ''you''.  Yinz is itself a contraction of the Appalachian dialect's ''[[you-uns]]''.

Compare [[y'all]].
